hunting /ˈhʌntɪŋ/

N-UNCOUNT Hunting is the chasing and killing of wild animals by people or other animals, for food or as a sport. 狩猎; 猎食 

例： He'd gone deer hunting with his cousins. 他已和堂兄弟们猎鹿去了。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Hunting is the activity of searching for a particular thing. 搜寻 

例： Job hunting should be approached as a job in itself. 找工作本身就应当被看作是一种工作。 

3. COMB in N-UNCOUNT Hunting is also a combining form. 寻求… (用于构词成分) 

例： Make job-hunting a full-time job until you find one. 在你找到工作之前，把求职当作一项全职工作。

</div>

